# Git merge and PR workflow

When merging pull requests, **preserve the branch's commit history**.

## Merge method

- **Default:** merge commit — `gh pr merge <number> --merge`
- **Never use `--squash`** unless the user explicitly asks for a squash merge
- **Never use `--rebase`** unless the user explicitly asks for rebase merge

## Examples

```bash
# ✅ Default — merge commit, keeps branch commits on main
gh pr merge 51 --merge --delete-branch

# ❌ Do not use unless explicitly requested
gh pr merge 51 --squash --delete-branch
```

## Rationale

Squash merges collapse branch history into one commit. This project keeps per-commit history on `main` for traceability (ticket refs, review follow-ups, etc.).
